The paper discusses the online visibility and impact of scientific research, specifically in the field of Biotechnology and Applied Microbiology, published by authors from Chinese affiliations. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), social computing (cs.SOC), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The focus on altmetric performance also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). However, given the specific context of the study, the first five sub-categories are more likely to be relevant.
